Police Minister Bheki Cele is expected to launch the festive season safety campaign in Mbombela, Mpumalanga. The Minister will conduct a roadblock in one of the provincial roads and visit taxi ranks in the province to assess the state of taxis and progress of the Safer Festive Season Operations. He is also expected to attend the pass out ceremony of traffic students at the Mpumalanga Traffic Training College in Bushbuckridge. Last week, Minister Cele together with Tourism Minister Mmamolo Kubayi-Ngubane announced a special comprehensive tourist safety plan for this festive season. It includes special training for tourism monitors by the police. 